defaultDistance.description: The default distance to position the target entity if hitTest is not available.

pointerPreviewEntity.description: (Optional) If set, an entity to be positioned on the current AR HitTest location.

useInput.description: If set to True, allow for input (mouse, touch) to scale this Entity.

scaleSensitivity.description: If useInput is set to True, how sensitive scaling is.

updateIntensity.description: If true, the intesity of the Light component will be updated based on the estimated light intensity value.

updateColor.description: If true, the color of the Light component will be updated based on the estimated light color value.

updateRotation.description: If true, the rotation of the Entity will be updated based on the estimated light rotation.

maxIntensity.description: If updateIntensity is set, cap the light intesity to this value.

orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster

distanceMax.title: Distance Max
distanceMax.description: Setting this at 0 will give an infinite distance limit

focusEntity.title: Focus Entity
focusEntity.description: Entity for the camera to focus on. If blank, then the camera will use the whole scene

frameOnStart.title: Frame on Start
frameOnStart.description: Frames the entity or scene at the start of the application."

inertiaFactor.title: Inertia Factor
inertiaFactor.description: Higher value means that the camera will continue moving after the user has stopped dragging. 0 is fully responsive.

autoRender.title: Auto Render
autoRender.description: Enable to render every frame. Disable to only render when camera is moving (saves power when the camera is still)

enableOnDefault.description: If set to true, this Entity will be Enabled when not in AR mode.

defaultCameraEntity.description: Entity with the scene's default, non-AR Camera.

arCameraEntity.description: Entity with a Camera component attached which is to be used for AR.

useLightEstimation.description: If set to true and available on device, use the LightEstimation API.

useHitTest.description: If set to true and available on device, use the HitTest API for placement of 3D objects on real-world geometry.

useInput.description: If set to true, listen to available device inputs for interacting with 3D scene objects (such as tapping on a phone).

orbitSensitivity.title: Orbit Sensitivity
orbitSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves around the orbit. Higher is faster

distanceSensitivity.title: Distance Sensitivity
distanceSensitivity.description: How fast the camera moves in and out. Higher is faster
